body:
The golden state warriors basketball team had something to prove all right. They plan to stay in the playoffs this year.
Thompson found his shooting touch and scored 27 points, making 11 of 13 shots while 7 footer JaVale McGee
contributed 15 points, 4 rebounds and 2 blocked shots in 16 minutes. 
Golden state came with the kind of swarming defense it is so used to playing in it's basketball games, but hadn't
exhibited much lately as rotations were mixed and matched because of injuries and illness.
